xxl.cursors
Class EnumerationCursor

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--xxl.cursors.EnumerationCursor
public class EnumerationCursor
extends Object
implements Cursor

This class is a wrapper for the old Enumeration class.
The constructor of this class receives a Enumeration-object by the caller and returns an EnumerationCursor. The Cursor-functionality is projected on Enumeration, therefore methods like: peek(), remove(), update() and reset() are not supported by EnumerationCursors.

See Also:
Enumeration, Cursor

Method Detail

close

public void close()
Closes the EnumerationCursor.
Signals the EnumerationCursor to cleanup resources, close files, etc.
After a call to close() calls to methods like next() or peek() are not guarantied to yield proper results.
Multiple calls to close() do not have any effect, i.e. if close() was called the EmptyCursor remains in the state "closed".
Implemenation is emtpy.
Specified by:
close in interface Cursor

hasNext

public boolean hasNext()
Returns true if the iteration has more elements.
(In other words, returns true if next or peek would return an element rather than throwing an exception.)
This method is implemented by calling the method hasMoreElements() (see: interface Enumeration) with the given enumeration-object.
